The chemical bath is a machine that has uses in and outside of ore processing;

In Ore Processing some variants of Crushed Ores can be turned into purified ores using this machine by bathing them in either
mercury or Sodium Persulfate. This is not too necessary unless you want to make specific byproducts.

The ore washer is a machine that works like a cauldron does for Ores; it can wash crushed ores into purified ores. It can also produce certain
byproducts as a result of this process;

E.g for a chance of getting Chrome you can wash Ruby ore into Purified ruby ore for a 33% chance for getting the dust.

Ore Processing in LV is not as simple as you think; Now, the Macerator still doesn't have any extra output slots, but from now on ore processing
will focus more on the byproducts found from processing certain ores;

A great example is Gallium Arsenide, which requires a lot of infastructure in Ore Processing to build.
